# zigbee_mgr component options.

menu "ZHAC zigbee_mgr"

config ZHAC_SPIKE_COORD_GROUP_JOIN
    bool "SPIKE: coordinator joins an APS group (native-groups Part B experiment)"
    default n
    help
      EXPERIMENTAL — leave OFF for production. Tests whether this radio's ZNP
      will let the coordinator RECEIVE groupcast frames that a hardware
      zone-remote (MiBoxer FUT089Z, groups 101-108) sends, so the remote's
      button presses reach the ZHAC rule engine.

      When enabled it (1) advertises the ZCL Groups (0x0004) cluster as an INPUT
      cluster on coordinator endpoint 1 (so the ZNP may instantiate a Groups
      server there), and (2) after init, loopback-sends a ZCL Add-Group command
      to the coordinator's own short address (0x0000) endpoint 1, attempting to
      join CONFIG_ZHAC_SPIKE_COORD_GROUP_ID.

      On a stock TI ZNP the ZCL layer runs on the host, so the loopback may only
      be delivered back as an AF_INCOMING frame rather than joining the group —
      that negative result is exactly what the spike measures. See
      extra/docs/NATIVE_ZCL_GROUPS_DESIGN.md (Part B).

config ZHAC_SPIKE_COORD_GROUP_ID
    int "SPIKE: group id the coordinator tries to join"
    depends on ZHAC_SPIKE_COORD_GROUP_JOIN
    default 101
    range 1 65535
    help
      MiBoxer FUT089Z maps zone 1 to group 101 by default. Set this to the group
      id of the zone button you will press during the test.

endmenu
